name: Rice Noodle Rolls with Shrimp and Chive #010
description: The silky and smooth texture of rice noodle rolls are a favorite among customers during yum cha! It is quite delicate and requires some advanced skill to make. The skin is made of rice flour and it is usually filled with various meat or veggies. The most popular filling for rice noodle rolls are pieces of dried shrimp and scallions. The dish is usually served with generous amount or a little of soy sauce. It is a very light dish compared to the other heavily fried dim sum dishes. At yum cha, it is often referred to as 'cheong fun' in Chinese!
